  "description": "SeizeIT2 is a multicenter prospective study validating wearable EEG (Sensor Dot device) in adult and pediatric patients with refractory epilepsy. The dataset comprises 125 patients from 5 European epilepsy monitoring units, containing approximately 11,640 hours of simultaneous wearable EEG, ECG, EMG, and movement data with 886 annotated focal seizure events recorded during presurgical evaluation.",
  "methods_description": "Participants with refractory epilepsy admitted for long-term video-EEG monitoring were recorded simultaneously with wearable Sensor Dot devices. The wearable EEG module (24.5 x 33.5 x 7.73 mm) was placed on the upper back with electrodes on the mastoid bone, sampling at 250 Hz. A second module on the chest recorded ECG and EMG at 250 Hz, with accelerometers and gyroscopes measuring movement at 25 Hz. EEG electrode placement (10-20 system or 25-electrode array) was individualized based on suspected seizure onset location.",
